<tr><td width="100%" valign="top" align="left" colspan="2"><p style="text-indent: 0; line-height: 100%; word-spacing: 0; margin: 0">&nbsp;</td></tr><tr><td width="100%" valign="top" align="left" colspan="2"><p style="text-indent: 0; line-height: 100%; word-spacing: 0; margin: 0"><img border="0" src="../triangle.JPG"><font size="3" face="Tahoma" color="#004242"><b>SOLOING IN THE OVERTHERE</b></font></td></tr><tr><td width="100%" valign="top" align="left" colspan="2"><p style="text-indent: 0; line-height: 100%; word-spacing: 0; margin: 0">&nbsp;</td></tr><tr><td width="20%" valign="top" align="left"><b><font size="2" face="Tahoma">Group / Solo:</font></b></td><td width="80%" valign="top" align="left"><font size="2" face="Tahoma">Solo - Shaman</font></td></tr><tr><td width="100%" valign="top" align="left" colspan="2"><p style="text-indent: 0; line-height: 100%; word-spacing: 0; margin: 0">&nbsp;</td></tr><tr><td width="20%" valign="top" align="left"><b><font size="2" face="Tahoma">Mob Level:</font></b></td><td width="80%" valign="top" align="left"><font size="2" face="Tahoma">32 to 42</font></td></tr><tr><td width="100%" valign="top" align="left" colspan="2"><p style="text-indent: 0; line-height: 100%; word-spacing: 0; margin: 0">&nbsp;</td></tr><tr><td width="20%" valign="top" align="left"><b><font size="2" face="Tahoma">Zone:</font></b></td><td width="80%" valign="top" align="left"><font size="2" face="Tahoma">Overthere</font></td></tr><tr><td width="100%" valign="top" align="left" colspan="2"><p style="text-indent: 0; line-height: 100%; word-spacing: 0; margin: 0">&nbsp;</td></tr><tr><td width="20%" valign="top" align="left"><b><font size="2" face="Tahoma">Location:</font></b></td><td width="80%" valign="top" align="left"><font size="2" face="Tahoma">n/a</font></td></tr><tr><td width="100%" valign="top" align="left" colspan="2"><p style="text-indent: 0; line-height: 100%; word-spacing: 0; margin: 0">&nbsp;</td></tr><tr><td width="20%" valign="top" align="left"><b><font size="2" face="Tahoma">Character Level:</font></b></td><td width="80%" valign="top" align="left"><font size="2" face="Tahoma">39 to 45</font></td></tr><tr><td width="100%" valign="top" align="left" colspan="2"><p style="text-indent: 0; line-height: 100%; word-spacing: 0; margin: 0">&nbsp;</td></tr><tr><td width="20%" valign="top" align="left"><b><font size="2" face="Tahoma">Strategy:</font></b></td><td width="80%" valign="top" align="left"><font size="2" face="Tahoma">From levels 39 to 45, you can solo in the Overthere as a Shaman pretty efficiently.  There are two methods of doing this, both good if used correctly.  I primarily used the first method, however.  It can be done almost anywhere in the zone where the higher level mobs roam, but I prefer either the Frontier Mountains zone line or the Skyfire zone line.  If you are an Iksar or Barbarian, beware of the roaming Dragoon guards who are most likely KoS to you..  they hit very hard, and cast spells, but you should be able to easily outrun them with SoW on.  I only died once to them during 5 levels of soloing here.
<br><br>
<b>First method</b>
<br><br>
Summon a pet, and make sure it's the best one you can summon.  Put Quickness/Alacrity on it, and also put your HP buff on both the pet and yourself.  Then throw Chloro on yourself as well. Med up to full, and tell your pet to guard here.  Run out and find a blue con mob, cast your Slow spell on it and run back to your pet.  Tell your pet to attack once you get within radius, and either re-cast Slow if it was resisted, or Venom of the Snake.  After this 2nd spell, the mob will probably come after you.  Melee it down, letting the pet and the DoT do the damage.  Cast the odd DD if you want, and back off to heal yourself if you need to.  You can customize your own way of doing this, but it's basically meleeing the mob with it slowed and DoT'd, after the fight, you will still have a lot of mana left, you should be able to get full health and full mana quickly with Chloroplast on.  For this method, I recommend turning your pets taunt off by typing /pet taunt off.
<br><br>
<b>Second method</b>
<br><br>
This method is a little bit trickier, but just as good if you can do it right.  Instead of tanking yourself, you let your pet tank instead while you meditate.  This is usually better once you get your Level 44 pet, but you can do it with some of the lower blues in the zone with a 39 pet.  Simply tell your pet to guard here, run out and pull something with Slow, and then tell your pet to attack.  The key here is to not over taunt the mob yourself, so it will stay on your pet.  Try waiting a few seconds for your pet to taunt the mob a couple of times, and then get up and cast Venom of the Snake.  Hopefully this will not cause it to hit you, but if it does, tank it for a couple of rounds and then back off, the pet should have taunted it enough by then.  Keep an eye on your pets health, and cast the odd DD.  If you can meditate throughout the fight, you should have plenty of mana.  Vary your methods to see what works best, everyone has their own way of doing things.
<br><br>
Final thoughts..  sometimes group experience is better than soloing in this zone, but you won't always find a very good balanced group to group with.  It is possible to solo here at 36 to 38, but it's not very good experience.  The loot here isn't TOO great, they do drop coin up to 4 plat and the odd item worth a plat or two though.  There is a LOT of roaming mobs in this zone, so I always found pulling constant low blues better experience than killing higher blues.  If you are a Troll or Ogre, you should be able to sell in the nearby outpost, otherwise you'll have to hold onto your loot for a while.  There is also a bank in the outpost.  I recommend printing out a map of the zone, just for reference.
<br><br>
Good luck!</font></td></tr><tr><td width="100%" valign="top" align="left" colspan="2"><p style="text-indent: 0; line-height: 100%; word-spacing: 0; margin: 0">&nbsp;</td></tr><tr><td width="20%" valign="top" align="left"><b><font size="2" face="Tahoma">Author:</font></b></td><td width="80%" valign="top" align="left"><font size="2" face="Tahoma">Kalday (Luclin)</font></td></tr><tr><td width="100%" valign="top" align="left" colspan="2"><p style="text-indent: 0; line-height: 100%; word-spacing: 0; margin: 0">&nbsp;</td></tr><tr><td width="20%" valign="top" align="left"><b><font size="2" face="Tahoma">Rating:</font></b></td><td width="80%" valign="top" align="left"><font size="2" face="Tahoma"><b>7.1</b> (average of <b>8</b> votes)</font></td></tr><tr><td width="100%" valign="top" align="left" colspan="2"><p style="text-indent: 0; line-height: 100%; word-spacing: 0; margin: 0">&nbsp;</td></tr><tr><td width="20%" valign="top" align="left" valign="middle"><b><font size="2" face="Tahoma">Rate this spot:</font></b></td><td width="80%" valign="top" align="left" valign="middle"><font size="2" face="Tahoma"><FORM ACTION = "ratehg.asp" METHOD = post><SELECT NAME="Voting"><OPTION VALUE="0">Rate this Spot</OPTION><OPTION VALUE="1">1 - Don't even bother</OPTION><OPTION VALUE="2">2</OPTION><OPTION VALUE="3">3</OPTION><OPTION VALUE="4">4</OPTION><OPTION VALUE="5">5 - It is ok</OPTION><OPTION VALUE="6">6</OPTION><OPTION VALUE="7">7</OPTION><OPTION VALUE="8">8</OPTION><OPTION VALUE="9">9</OPTION><OPTION VALUE="10">10 - You must come here</OPTION></SELECT><INPUT TYPE = "hidden" NAME = "intHGID" VALUE = 35><INPUT TYPE = "submit" VALUE="Rate It!"></form></font></td></tr><tr><td width="100%" valign="top" align="left" colspan="2"><p style="text-indent: 0; line-height: 100%; word-spacing: 0; margin: 0">&nbsp;</td></tr><tr><td width="100%" valign="top" align="left" colspan="2"><p style="text-indent: 0; line-height: 100%; word-spacing: 0; margin: 0">&nbsp;</td></tr><div align="center"><center><table border="0" cellpadding="0" cellspacing="0" width="70%"><tr><td width="100%" valign="top" align="center" bgcolor="#004242"><p style="text-indent: 0; line-height: 100%; word-spacing: 0; margin: 0"><font size="2" face="Tahoma" color="#FFFFFF"><b>Comments for this Guide</b></font></td></tr><tr><td width="100%" valign="top" align="left"><p style="text-indent: 0; line-height: 100%; word-spacing: 0; margin: 0">&nbsp;</td></tr><tr><td width="100%" valign="top" align="left"><p style="text-indent: 0; line-height: 100%; word-spacing: 0; margin: 0"><font size="2" face="Tahoma" color="#004242"><b>LOOT</font><font size="2" face="Tahoma"></b> - by <b>Stormrage</b> on 2/3/03</font></td></tr><tr><td width="100%" valign="top" align="left"><p style="text-indent: 0; line-height: 100%; word-spacing: 0; margin: 0"><font size="2" face="Tahoma">One last thing. The loot here at this level is crap. If you're here for xp AND loot, it's a 6/10 rating. Xp only will bring it to 9/10 for how easy it is, and how little risk there is involved. Depending on the level of importance you place on xp vs loot.</td></tr><tr><td width="100%" valign="top" align="left"><p style="text-indent: 0; line-height: 100%; word-spacing: 0; margin: 0">&nbsp;</td></tr><tr><td width="100%" valign="top" align="left"><p style="text-indent: 0; line-height: 100%; word-spacing: 0; margin: 0"><font size="2" face="Tahoma" color="#004242"><b>ERG SQUARED...</font><font size="2" face="Tahoma"></b> - by <b>Stormrage</b> on 2/3/03</font></td></tr><tr><td width="100%" valign="top" align="left"><p style="text-indent: 0; line-height: 100%; word-spacing: 0; margin: 0"><font size="2" face="Tahoma">I meant the post below. *sigh*</td></tr><tr><td width="100%" valign="top" align="left"><p style="text-indent: 0; line-height: 100%; word-spacing: 0; margin: 0">&nbsp;</td></tr><tr><td width="100%" valign="top" align="left"><p style="text-indent: 0; line-height: 100%; word-spacing: 0; margin: 0"><font size="2" face="Tahoma" color="#004242"><b>ERG....</font><font size="2" face="Tahoma"></b> - by <b>Stormrage</b> on 2/3/03</font></td></tr><tr><td width="100%" valign="top" align="left"><p style="text-indent: 0; line-height: 100%; word-spacing: 0; margin: 0"><font size="2" face="Tahoma">Sorry about the UNFORMATTED post above everyone. I *was* formatted when I typed it in. Now I know it's a right royal pain to read. *sigh*</td></tr><tr><td width="100%" valign="top" align="left"><p style="text-indent: 0; line-height: 100%; word-spacing: 0; margin: 0">&nbsp;</td></tr><tr><td width="100%" valign="top" align="left"><p style="text-indent: 0; line-height: 100%; word-spacing: 0; margin: 0"><font size="2" face="Tahoma" color="#004242"><b>KITING FROM LVL 32</font><font size="2" face="Tahoma"></b> - by <b>Stormrage</b> on 2/3/03</font></td></tr><tr><td width="100%" valign="top" align="left"><p style="text-indent: 0; line-height: 100%; word-spacing: 0; margin: 0"><font size="2" face="Tahoma">Nonono. The post above is just too cautious. I know that Druids can kite from 28 or so here, and quad kite later on, but here's how my Barb Sham has been at it.

I've been kiting here since I was level 32. You still have the same spells from when you dinged 29, but the difference is that you get resisted way less. At such a low level however, (and without Scourge - 533 dmg Disease DOT), you will likely require KEI - it's a gamble without KEI. With or without KEI, you should have your HP buffs, SOW (oh der), Regen, Cann I - dex if you want, for less interruption, and Ag & Protect for more AC. Grab blues only, no yellows or whites /cons.

Before you reach 34 and get your first pet spell (Summon Companion), kiting will go something like: Envenomed Breath to pull, run, Affliction, run, Tainted breath, run, root, Cann, med, Cann, med, etc. Repeat when root wears out, or when a DOT wears out. Try not to overlap, as it'll be a waste of mana, and you'll need all the mana you have to kill the mob. Don't Cann more than 2 bubbs away, or your margin for error will be all the more thinner. The best place I know to kite is the valley at the Ledge, leading to the FM zone. No adds, ever... Unless someone trained mobs/Goons in.

If you DO have KEI, then it's a cinch. Don't even need to root - nuke the mob once in a while when you've run far enough. This only works against Succulents and Cocatrices, and MOST Sarnaks - some Sarnak Knights move FAST, and ALL Rhinos and Sabres will keep up with your sowed movement. Leave the Rhinos and Sabres for the groupies.

LEVEL 34+ - From here it's even faster. Scourge is now yours, and Tainted Breath is a thing of the past. Scourge once, Affliction once, Envenomed breath twice, couple of nukes, and voila. You may need to Instill/Root before casting Scourge, as it takes AGES to cast this spell, but since you're pulling with it, you don't need to cast instill/root - do this only if the mob resisted the initial Scourge.

OR, if you're mana-stingy (and don't like downtime at all, even with KEI - small amount of downtime after about 5 mobs if you have KEI) - have your pet handy. Turn taunt off (/pet taunt off). Buff up your pet with attack buffs (Quickness, Strength), and perhaps some HP ones JUST IN CASE (Health, T'Narg, Shield, Agi, Inner Fire). Scourge (to pull), run, Affliction, run, /pet attack, Envenomed Breath. The Envenomed Breath should take the Mob's aggro off your pet. This is VITAL. Your pet would last 15 seconds against these mobs, if that. If you don't have aggro, nuke it until you have it. Walk/run away from the mob, while your pet is still hitting it. This will further damage and slow down the mob. Don't pull too far away or your pet will get aggro, and DIE. That'd just be a waste of mana. If pet gets aggro, hotfoot it back, and nuke/reDOT to retain aggro.

Using the last method, you can handle ALL Sarnaks, Succulents, and Cockatrices - even ones that /con RED. Just go for it. You can even do Rhinos and Sabres, but it's really annoying, as they tend to run too fast (still), AND Sabres have higher resist. Try to use Instill rather than root, as it sticks more, and lasts longer. This should all burn between 1 to 2.5 bubbs of mana, closer to 1.5.

I'm lvl 35 now, and there are no more red mobs near the Ledge (except, of course, Dragoons), and still doing this.

I have NEVER died in OT using the above method. If you're sensible, neither will you. Wait until lvl 39 with a better pet, VoS, etc. Mmmmmm. Too easy.

